RESULTS: Bulbar phenotype correlated with older age (p {\textless} 0.0001), women were more affected than men at increasing age (p {\textless} 0.0001), classic with younger age (p = 0.029), men were more affected than women at increasing age (p {\textless} 0.0001), PUMN with younger age (p {\textless} 0.0001), flail arm with male sex (p {\textless} 0.0001) and younger age (p = 0.04), flail leg with male sex with increasing age (p = 0.008), and respiratory with male sex (p {\textless} 0.0001). C9orf72 expansions correlated with bulbar phenotype (p {\textless} 0.0001), and were less frequent in PUMN (p = 0.041); SOD1 mutations correlated with flail leg phenotype (p {\textless} 0.0001), and were less frequent in bulbar (p {\textless} 0.0001). ALS-FTD correlated with C9orf72 (p {\textless} 0.0001) and bulbar phenotype (p = 0.008), ALScbi with PUMN (p = 0.014), and ALSci with older age (p = 0.008).
